RACE.RACE_TEXT: Maryland Million Distaff S. LAUREL PARK RACE 10 7F Dirt CR: 97. Stakes Purse 100000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES, THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: INTREPID DAYDREAM , confidently handled four wide outside rivals tracking the pace, dropped in a bit and cruised up to engage RESPONSE TIME heading to the quarter pole, took command soon into the lane, powered away under a drive past mid stretch then held sway while kept alert to the wire. RESPONSE TIME took command leaving the chute and handled some outside pressure while under rating, edged clear leaving the far turn, dug in when confronted by the winner near the quarter pole, shifted out when not quite able to keep pace in mid stretch, straightened away and kept on well to preserve the place. LUNA BELLE , off a bit slow, settled off the pace, edged up between runners near the half mile marker, angled out four to five wide for the drive then closed steadily while on her left lead. MAVILUS , off the pace while saving ground, continued inside into the stretch, moved up some past mid stretch then flattened out very late. FILLE D'ESPRIT , with the pace three wide between runners, came under a ride mid turn, shifted out four wide approaching the stretch, failed to kick on past the three sixteenths and faded. MALIBU BEAUTY was used up when rushing between rivals to contest the pace, saw the leaders get away past the five sixteenths and weakened. QUIET IMAGINATION lacked speed, raced three wide near the half, circled four wide into the stretch but failed to rally. SWEET GRACIE , well placed towards the inside stalking the quartet of leaders, came under a ride past the three eighths, eased out three wide for the drive, lacked a punch and retreated through the final furlong.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Maryland Million Classic S. LAUREL PARK RACE 11 1 1/8M Dirt CR: 106. Stakes Purse 150000. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MARKET MAVEN chased the pace down the backstretch, was two wide on the turn, floated out a bit entering the stretch, bid for the lead in upper stretch, bumped AIN'T DA BEER COLD when angled in inside the eighth pole and narrowly prevailed. AIN'T DA BEER COLD , sent to the early lead, set the pace along the inner rail, was bothered in mid stretch and battled gamely in a sharp effort. DOUBLE CROWN , patiently handled between horses down the backstretch, eased out to the four path leaving the far turn, had aim on the lead in upper stretch and flattened out. DOLICE VITA hugged the inner rail down the backstretch stalking the pace, saved ground the far turn and gave way in upper stretch. ALL THREES stalked the pace outside horses down the backstretch, circled the far turn three wide and gave way turning for home. LOOSE ENDS lacked speed, circled the far turn four wide, floated to the five path in upper stretch and gave way. RHUMJAR , between horses the first turn, was never a factor. OURNATIONONPARADE bobbled leaving the first turn, gave way and returned bleeding. Following an objection by the rider of AIN'T DA BEER COLD, MARKET MAVEN was disqualified and placed second.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BONDED rated outside a rival in a stalking spot, steadily progressed four wide to take aim on the leaders into the lane, leveled off when switching to his correct lead leaving the furlong grounds, collared IMAGINE IT ALL inside the sixteenth pole, kept on doggedly to gain a slim advantage in deep stretch then got the bob at the wire. IMAGINE IT ALL , reluctant to load, moved up widest to take over heading to the first turn, cleared and dropped in to set the pace, was joined by SEVILLE ROW mid way on the final turn, responded to firm asks and kicked back clear in upper stretch, drifted out maintaining the advantage past the furlong grounds, dug back in when confronted by the winner leaving the sixteenth marker, dueled valiantly inside that one but lost the bob. BOFFO KID steadied back off foes soon after the break, edged up three wide near the half, moved up five wide under a hustling ride in upper stretch and found his best stride in the final furlong to bridge the gap. SEVILLE ROW prompted in hand outside the leader, bid to challenge after six furlongs, forced the issue into the stretch, couldn't quite quicken past mid stretch then gave way grudgingly. THE LAST SCIP checked heading to the first turn, saved ground through the backstretch run, eased out past the five sixteenths, advanced between runners in mid stretch then continued with effort. NICK PAPAGIORGIO saved ground, eased out and raced in range in upper stretch but failed to seriously kick on. SOROLLA lagged far back, saved ground most of the way and offered a response through the lane. MINT GAME broke a bit slow, settled off the pace, raced four wide between rivals nearing the quarter pole, angled out but lacked a rally. BRILLIANT CHASE angled off the rail soon into the backstretch, moved up steadily while between rivals heading to the turn, chased under a hearty ride past the five sixteenths then faded. REMEMBERING WILBUR angled out early into the backstretch run, lost ground four to five wide from the far turn and came up empty. SIGMUND failed to menace. PRIDE OF PAYTON , forward inside early on, steadied off heels into the first turn, regrouped and stalked inside, gave hard pursuit past the five sixteenths and weakened. JACKSON MAN broke awkwardly, raced wide off the pace and lacked a rally. RUN ROCKY RUN lost ground four to six wide while outside rivals, moved up some past the three eighths, chased to upper stretch then retreated.
